<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626552>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–3. Omma stanleyi: 1, Natural habitat, Queensland, Australia ©Dash Huang (17 Jan 2017); 2–3, habitus: 2, dorsal (♀ 20 mm, VIC); 3, same, ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626552/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626558>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–21. Omma stanleyi: 14–19. Head (♀): 14, dorsal, 15, ventral, 16, lateral, 17, frontal, 18, mandible, dorsal; 19, Beutelius rutherfordi (paratype ♂): labial palp; 20, B. mastersi (♀): maxilla; 21, O. stanleyi: head, latero-ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626558/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626566>
    dc:description "FIGURES 39–44. Omma stanleyi (♀): 39–43. 39, pronotum, 40, prothorax, ventral, 41–42, prothorax, lateral, 43, scutellum; 44, Beutelius rutherfordi, prothorax, lateral (paratype ♂)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626566/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626570>
    dc:description "FIGURES 51–55. Omma stanleyi (♀): 51, pterothorax, ventral; 52, pterothorax, latero-ventral; 53, pterothorax and hind legs; 54, bifid mesoventral process; 55, abdominal ventrites 1 and 2 (in part)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626570/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626572>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–63. Beutelius sagitta (♂): 56, epipleuron, ventral view; B. rutherfordi (♂): 57, epipleuron, ventral view; O. stanleyi (♀) elytron: 58–60, 63. 58, ventral view with epipleuron, 59, dorsal, 60, internal, 63 dorsal; B. mastersi (♀) elytron: 61–62. 61, dorsal, 62, ventral view with epipleuron." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626572/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626574>
    dc:description "FIGURES 64–66. Omma stanleyi (♀) wing: 64, complete view; 65, wing base (in folded wing); 66, wing, apical field, with apical wing folding. Veinal nomenclature abbreviations: BR: radial basivenale. BM: redial basivenale. BCu: cubital basivenale. AA: anal anterior. AP: anal posterior. Cu: cubitus. C: costa. ScA: subcosta anterior. ScP: subcosta posterior. RA: radius anterior. RP: radius posterior. MP: media posterior. WC: wedge cell. BC: brachial cell. Cross-veins: rp-mp, r, cv1: mp3+4-cua, cv2: mp1+2-mp3+4, cv3: mp1+2-mp3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626574/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626576>
    dc:description "FIGURES 67–70. Beutelius mastersi (♂): 67, wing (veinal nomenclature as in Fig. 64); B. sagitta (♂): 68, wing; Omma stanleyi: 69–70. 69, elytron base, 70, elytron, close detail of sutural flange." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626576/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626578>
    dc:description "FIGURES 71–75. Omma stanleyi and Beutelius spp. abdominal ventrites and tergites: 71, B. rutherfordi (♂, holotype); 72, B. mastersi (♀) ventrites; 73, B. sagitta (♂) ventrites; 74, O. stanleyi (♀) ventrites; 75, B. sagitta (♂), tergites." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626578/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626580>
    dc:description "FIGURES 76–84. Omma stanleyi (♀): 76–78. 76, foreleg, 77, midleg, 78, hind leg. Forelegs (♂): 79–84. 79, Beutelius rutherfordi; 80–81, O. stanleyi, 80, anterior view, 81, lateral view; 82–83, B. sagitta, 82, anterior view, 83, posterior view; 84, B. mastersi, anterior view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626580/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3626582>
    dc:description "FIGURES 85–95. Beutelius spp., mentum: 85–86. 85, B. mastersi, 86, B. rutherfordi (paratype ♂); 87, B. mastersi, mesonotum; 88, B. mastersi, pterothorax, ventral; 89, B. rutherfordi, pterothorax, ventral; aedeagus: 90–95. 90, Omma stanleyi; 91–92, B. mastersi; 93, B. reidi sp. nov.; 94, B. rutherfordi; 95, B. sagitta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3626582/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

